{
  "stem": "14060.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And being a city of about 60,000 people, there were approximately 1,800 Jewish souls.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That means from babies to old people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So therefore, there was only one primary school, Jewish primary school, which both communities' children attended to, as it was legal and obligatory for people to go to school.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And interestingly enough, the arrangement in the school was, whilst it was mainly supervised or run by the Neolog community, nevertheless, the Orthodox community was accommodated by the mere fact that the girls sat in the front rows and the boys in behind.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was a perfectly normal primary school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It has not affected anybody's additional requirements to study any Hebrew subject.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Some were obviously taught.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Presumably, the Orthodox community required a little bit more, which then people, like in my case, we individually had private lessons.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Or some attended to a Talmud Torah, which was also in the school in town.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The actual school was situated pretty well in the center of town, next to the Neolog shul, which was quite a nice edifice.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It doesn't exist today because it was bombed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And presently, I think there is a block of flats being built on it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We lived in a very nice part of town, which was called [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It was a park, which had houses and residences on either side of the park.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The family originate not very far from Sopron, a place called Ebergoetz, which, in my childhood, I visited only once or twice.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The history-- this is basically a family story-- is that, as you know, in the Austro-Hungarian Empire, Jews were only allowed to live in the small villages up to the time of emancipation.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
